Weather this happens or not questionable being I have no clue what VI has in store. Lots of rumors about epic upgrades.<br>
<br>
The level of Epic pet needs to be raised.  I think it should be done progressively directly relating to the progression of ones char. <br>
<br>
The cast time and recast restrictions need to go. With the new mobs in PoP those restrictions dont mean a hill of beans.  So long as mana cost is 500 there isnt going to be much a difference as to wheather I chain epic or chain 61 air pet.  DS isnt a factor in chaining because epic will not cast shield during the immediatelly ensuing combat.<br>
<br>
I would like to see AA and quests geared specifically at improvement of the epic.  Epic is something a lot of mages myself included spent time to aquire.  I have noticed many mages now unscribing the spell completely for the new pets.  I am the only mage in guild out of 4 who uses Epic over new water pet on raids and in groups.  The mages on the server without epic have begun to shun the Epic quest in light of the new pets.  I certainly dont want to see a year and half of eq time gone to rot in the back of my spell book.  That doesnt mean nerf the new pets because they do not unblance the game.  Nor should it mean that we be rewarded continually for past accomplishments.  Merely give us an opportunity to build on something we already worked so hard for. <br>
<br>
